        "created_at": "2018-06-18T20:27:53.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Elevated levels of VA can certainly lead to an acrid taste on the finish - but you would most likely notice something aromatically in this case. You might get a whiff of \u2018vinegar\u2019 or \u2018balsamic\u2019 - or I\u2019ve known some that noticed a \u2018burn\u2019 in their nose.</p>\n<p>Tough to say that it\u2019s a slight case of TCA - just seems like this is becoming a \u2018catch all\u2019 for bottle variation.</p>\n<p>Cheers.</p>",
