        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/d.callahan/{size}/1026_2.png",
        "created_at": "2018-06-18T22:49:33.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Thanks for the input guys. The nose was pretty nice but not as big as the first bottle I tasted a few years ago and there was no wet cardboard smell whatsoever so I didn\u2019t immediately think TCA. The wine came across as super alcoholic on the finish but a hint of TCA seems to be the best answer. I hate the old \u201cbottle variation\u201d reason since it is so random. Oh well, it is what it is!</p>\n<p>Thanks again.</p>",
