      {
        "id": 2434377,
        "name": "larry schaffer",
        "username": "larry_schaffer",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/larry_schaffer/{size}/447_2.png",
        "created_at": "2018-06-19T01:15:14.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I think the old adage stands true here. There are no great wines, only great bottles.</p>\n<p>It still seems a reach to call this slight TCA in my opinion. And comparing one bottle to the next few years apart is pretty darn challenging.</p>\n<p>Do you know anyone who is really really really sensitive to TCA? Perhaps you can have him or her smell it, but do not give them the indication you think it might be corked.</p>\n<p>Good luck and it is a bummer that this didn\u2019t live up to your expectations.</p>\n<p>Cheers!</p>",
